      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "s = input()\n\nr = []\nfor i in range(len(s)):\n    if s[i].isdigit():\n        if i == 0:\n            nv = ord(s[i + 1])\n        elif i == len(s) - 1:\n            nv = ord(s[i - 1])\n        else:\n            nv = ord(s[i - 1]) + ord(s[i + 1])\n        \n        r.append(str(nv))\n    else:\n        r.append(s[i])\n\nprint(''.join(r))\n",
      "statement": "Given a string [[S]] consisting of lowercase letters and digits, replace each digit in the string with the sum of the ASCII values of its neighboring characters. If a digit is at the start or end of the string, replace it with the ASCII value of its only neighbor.",
